  "response": "Certainly! Here are some sentence examples using the word \"contemporary\":\n\n1. **Cultural Context**: \"The museum features a mix of classical art and contemporary works by modern artists.\"\n\n2. **Time Period**: \"Shakespeare\u2019s plays remain relevant even in our contemporary society.\"\n\n3. **Comparison**: \"While her writing style is contemporary, it also pays homage to classic literary traditions.\"\n\n4. **Design**: \"The architect designed a contemporary house with sleek lines and an open floor plan.\"\n\n5. **Society**: \"Contemporary issues like climate change and digital privacy dominate global discussions.\"\n\n6. **Music**: \"Her playlist includes both contemporary pop hits and timeless classics.\"\n\n7. **Fashion**: \"The designer\u2019s latest collection blends contemporary trends with vintage influences.\"\n\n8. **Historical Context**: \"The novel provides a contemporary perspective on life during the industrial revolution.\"\n\n9. **Artistic Influence**: \"Many contemporary filmmakers are inspired by the visual styles of the 1980s.\"\n\n10. **Philosophy**: \"His ideas on ethics are rooted in ancient philosophy but are still applicable in contemporary debates.\"\n\nLet me know if you'd like more examples!",
